        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='20332' hidden='true' id='6' story-point-id='1' type-v2='text' w='48524' x='3937' y='20539'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Bold'>This results help to examines the differences in sleep duration, screen use, and work patterns between urban and rural residents in Bhutan to understand how these lifestyle factors influence overall health and wellbeing. </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='17427' hidden='true' id='7' story-point-id='1' type-v2='text' w='43799' x='53642' y='39419'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe UI'>Take care of yourself first</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe UI' italic='true'>or you will have nothing left to give others.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe UI'>Self-care is not selfishness.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe UI' italic='true'>You cannot serve it from an empty vessel.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='3112' hidden='true' id='8' story-point-id='1' type-v2='text' w='21457' x='37598' y='14834'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontsize='16'>Health and Wellbeing</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='33402' hidden='true' id='10' story-point-id='7' type-v2='text' w='33268' x='64567' y='15560'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe UI' fontsize='11'>The survey collected 366 responses providing insights into the lifestyle and work patterns of residents in Bhutan. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe UI' fontsize='11'>Among respondents, more are female than male, with a small number not reporting gender. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe UI' fontsize='11'>Most live in urban areas compared to rural areas, while some did not specify their location. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe UI' fontsize='11'>The majority of participants report engaging in both physical and mental work, whereas smaller groups report only physical or only mental work.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='77801' hidden='true' id='9' story-point-id='9' type-v2='text' w='32874' x='82579' y='14419'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe UI' fontsize='11'>The dashboard shows the distribution of respondents and key lifestyle patterns between rural and urban residents in Bhutan. Most respondents are from urban areas of the 366 responses collected in the survey. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe UI' fontsize='11'>The comparison of average working hours, screen use before sleep, and sleep hours shows small differences between rural and urban residents. Urban residents tend to work slightly longer hours compared to rural residents. Meanwhile, rural residents report slightly higher screen use before sleep than urban residents. In terms of sleep duration, both groups show very similar patterns with only a small difference between them.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe UI' fontsize='11'>The findings shows that increased screen exposure before bedtime and longer working hours may affect sleep quality and daytime energy levels. These lifestyle habits can influence how well individuals rest at night and how energetic they feel during the day. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe UI' fontsize='11'>In short , the survey of 366 Bhutanese residents shows more urban than rural participants. Urban residents work slightly longer hours, while rural residents use screens a bit more before sleep. Sleep duration is similar across both groups. Longer work hours and higher screen time before bed lower sleep quality and daytime energy.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='49274' id='11' story-point-id='11' type-v2='text' w='33268' x='80512' y='32469'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe UI' fontsize='11'>The chosen habit for improving sleep quality is reducing screen use before bedtime, followed by creating a stress-free environment and maintaining a consistent sleep schedule. This is followed by engaging in relaxing activities and exercising regularly, while avoiding caffeine late and using alarm reminders are chosen less often.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe UI' fontsize='11'>For support features in a sleep application, reminders to reduce screen use are chosen first, followed by sleep tracking statistics and tips for better bedtime. This is followed by features that help manage schedules, provide sleep education, and offer relaxation or breathing support, while SMS reminders are chosen less frequently.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Segoe UI' fontsize='11'>For future app use, the option “maybe” is chosen first, followed by “yes,” while “no” is selected the least.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <simple-id uuid='{9B2190AB-4D2B-488C-A482-4CEBBCBCF4DA}' />
    </dashboard>
  </dashboards>
